        <title>Steps to Meaningful Assessment</title>
        <contents>&lt;p&gt;The following reading by Linda Suskie explores seven steps for creating assessments that provide students with opportunities to demonstrate what they have learned in meaningful ways.   As you read we ask you to consider how assessment activities and systems can and should be helpful to students. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a title="Fair Assessment Practices" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/ABT1R1-Fair%20Assessment%20Practices.pdf"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 1.231;"&gt;&lt;i&gt;F&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 1.231;"&gt;&lt;i&gt;air Assessment Practices: Giving Students Equitable Opportunities to Demonstrate Learning&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;Adventures in Assessment&lt;/span&gt;, by Linda Suskie, Volume 14, Spring 2002.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b style="line-height: 1.231;"&gt;Questions for Discussion:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now we ask you to consider the following questions and discuss them with your peers:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What is one thing you learned from this article that you would like to apply to your practice?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What questions or concerns does this article raise for you?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How does the article support your current assessment or instructional practices?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;b&gt;_____________________________________________________________________&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
